        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(harness): add Codex pre-tool loop relay opt-out",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a narrow opt-out for Codex Harness loop-detection-only native PreToolUse relay subprocesses:\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    loopDetection: {\n      nativePreToolUseRelay: false,\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nDefault behavior is preserved. If the new field is unset, Codex Harness keeps the existing native PreToolUse relay behavior unless `tools.loopDetection.enabled` is explicitly `false`.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nCodex Harness bridges Codex native hook callbacks into OpenClaw through command hooks. For PreToolUse, that can install an `openclaw hooks relay` command hook before every tool call so OpenClaw can run before-tool policy / loop-detection checks.\n\nOn tool-heavy Codex Harness runs, the loop-detection-only path creates repeated short-lived OpenClaw CLI subprocesses. Codex ACP does not use this same native-hook relay path.\n\nThe intended fix is not to globally disable loop detection or change default behavior. It gives harness users one explicit switch, `tools.loopDetection.nativePreToolUseRelay=false`, to skip the loop-detection-only native PreToolUse relay while preserving other policy and trusted-tool paths.\n\n## Changes\n\nThe PR keeps the scope intentionally small:\n\n- Adds `tools.loopDetection.nativePreToolUseRelay?: boolean` to config parsing and config help metadata.\n- Makes the harness relay predicate return false for loop-detection-only PreToolUse work when `nativePreToolUseRelay=false`.\n- Threads that decision into the Codex app-server overlay so inactive PreToolUse becomes `hooks.PreToolUse=[]` instead of an `openclaw hooks relay --pre-tool-use-unavailable noop` command hook.\n- Preserves explicit `before_tool_call` / trusted policy relay behavior.\n\nNo docs pages are changed in this PR; the public surface is limited to schema/help metadata plus runtime behavior and tests.\n\n## Config behavior\n\n- `nativePreToolUseRelay=false`: disables loop-detection-only native PreToolUse relay subprocess installation.\n- unset or `true`: preserves current behavior.\n- `tools.loopDetection.enabled=false`: still disables broader loop-detection behavior, but this PR does not require that broader switch.\n\n## Evidence\n\nCurrent PR head before the lint-only follow-up: `3a09080f`.\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-hook-relay.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.turn-watches.test.ts` -> 4 files passed, 228 tests passed.\n- `git diff --check` -> passed.\n- CI failure investigation: `check-lint` only flagged one style issue in `src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.ts` (`no-unnecessary-boolean-literal-compare`); the follow-up keeps the same behavior using `?? true`.\n\nRegression coverage includes both layers that matter:\n\n- Harness relay: `nativePreToolUseRelay=false` makes `shouldRelayEvent(\"pre_tool_use\")` false.\n- Codex app-server overlay: when inactive PreToolUse hook installation is disabled, generated config contains `hooks.PreToolUse=[]` rather than a no-op relay command hook.\n",
        "branch": "fix/codex-harness-loop-detection-relay-default",
